        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "When creating an action named foo-bar I would expect the action name in the controller to be camel cased, but instead it keeps the action name as is.\r\n\r\nThis causes an error with the CLI when you try to create another action on the same controller:\r\nParse error: syntax error, unexpected '-', expecting '(' \r\n\r\nThe view scripts are correctly left as is."
