        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36606",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=theashman",
                        "name": "theashman",
                        "displayName": "Ashley Broadley",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "if you think about it from an OO perspective, each action is a method of a class.\r\nso calling index action of index controller calls:\r\nIndexController::indexAction()\r\n\r\nif you called an action 'test-action'\r\nthen it would call:\r\nIndexController::test-actionAction()\r\n\r\nthe hyphen character is not a valid method naming character, therefore this is not a bug.\r\nif you want to have hyphenated urls, consider using Zend_Controller_Router_Route_Static, or a rewrite rule in your .htaccess\r\n\r\nurls initially map to \/controllername\/actionname\r\n\r\ncalling ControllernameController::actionnameAction, if Zend_Tool was to camel case the action name then it would have to also create a rewrite rule\/static route so you could access the hyphenated action. I think this would be cause Zend_Tool to undertake too much work by having to generate extra code.\r\n\r\n* sorry for all the edits, it's early",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=theashman",
                        "name": "theashman",
                        "displayName": "Ashley Broadley",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-01T01:14:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-01T01:15:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36612",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mark_79_smith",
                        "name": "mark_79_smith",
                        "displayName": "Mark Smith",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I did not expect the method to be named with the hypen, I expected it to be camel-cased.\r\n\r\nSo if I called an action test-action in the index controller\r\nit would call IndexController::testActionAction()\r\nnot\r\nIndexController::testactionAction()\r\n\r\nI understand the use of Routers so I am happy to use them.\r\n\r\nHowever, I feel Zend Tool should block the input of illegal characters.\r\nIdeally this should be done when creating a controller and action.\r\n\r\nMy other issue is that part camel-cased action names look wrong, but that's just my opinion :)\r\n\r\nWhat are your thoughts?\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mark_79_smith",
                        "name": "mark_79_smith",
                        "displayName": "Mark Smith",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-01T11:24:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-01T11:24:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40768",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralf",
                        "name": "ralf",
                        "displayName": "Ralf Eggert",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Can be closed I think. When I try to add a hyphenated action, I get an error message as expected.\r\n\r\nzf create action foo-bar user\r\n\r\nAn Error Has Occurred \r\nAction names should be camel cased.         ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralf",
                        "name": "ralf",
                        "displayName": "Ralf Eggert",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-29T08:20:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-29T08:20:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/42648",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This was fixed with the \"canonicalization\" of names patch in 1.10 (I am pretty sure that is when that error message came in).\r\n\r\n-ralph",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
